1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,400
Forces come in pairs — rockets push exhaust, exhaust pushes rockets.

2
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:07,200
This is Newton's third law of motion.

3
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:10,400
Every action has an equal and opposite reaction.

4
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:12,400
Imagine a rocket in space.

5
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:16,000
It expels gas downward and, boom, it shoots up!

6
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:20,800
This principle explains not just rockets but swimming, walking, and even flying.

7
00:00:20,800 --> 00:00:28,400
So, every time you push off the ground, remember: you’re not just moving forward, you’re pushing against the Earth!

8
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:30,800
Want to explore more science concepts?

9
00:00:30,800 --> 00:00:33,200
Hit follow for more amazing insights!
